name: John Yerkes
text: We’ve loved the Brookside location and were thrilled to see them open closer to home in Leawood. They’ve yet to have their grand opening, but we thoroughly enjoyed our dinner. Star of the show was the Salmon. Can’t wait for them to hit their stride.
title: Plate Restaurant - Leawood

name: Veronica Kindersmith
text:
Went here for my husband's birthday! Everyone here was very kind and made sure to celebrate him. The food was absolutely delicious, spritz' were great, what can I say? This is one of the best upscale restaurants in Town Center Plaza.

I have to make a separate paragraph for the dessert. Nikki did a fantastic job. It's a peanut butter custard with brownie cubes and buttered pecans. One of the best desserts I've eaten!
title: Plate Restaurant - Leawood

name: Norma Arnold
text: DELISH!! Let’s start with the donuts. The DONUTS! The right amount of sweet and savory to let you know you’ve had a donut, but doesn’t guilt you into feeling like you can’t have anything else to eat. They were fantastic. I had the chicken and risotto. The risotto was creamy and delicious and the chicken was fried to perfection. Others in my party got biscuits and gravy, pizza, and the carbonara. Everyone said their dishes were great. The potatoes that came with the B&G got great feedback, as well. A great place to go with your girls, your fellas, or even by yourself! Check them out. You won’t be disappointed!!
title: Plate Restaurant - Leawood

name: John Hill
text: We had reservations for dinner during restaurant week and when we arrived, we were seated promptly. The restaurant was pretty full, but it wasn't too loud. Our waiter did a great job taking care of us and giving recommendations. We started with appetizers of meatballs, Pear Bruschetta and Salmon Crudo. It was a great way to start off our meal. For entrees we had Rigatoni Bolognese, Tuscan Chicken and Salmon. We shared bites and I would order any of  the other items next time I come here. I enjoyed the hand made pasta and you could tell they paid attention to details. The dessert was Tiramisu and it was ok, nothing special. Their wine and beer selection is decent. Overall, a great dinner and I recommend  to come with some friends and the night will be memorable.  I am looking forward to coming back and trying other options on the menu.
title: Plate Restaurant - Leawood

name: Tami McCracken
text:
My husband and I had our anniversary dinner here and it was amazing! The service from the time we walked in was incredible. They sat us immediately and the waiter was very prompt. The chef, Jeff, greeted us personally and even presented our dessert for us!
My husband had the chicken, which was flavorful and juicy. I had pasta with shrimp, which I recommend highly! We had the pear bruschetta appetizer and I would also highly recommend it!
It was a very enjoyable evening and plan to go back again!
title: Plate Restaurant - Leawood

name: Jim Tompkins
text: Celebrated my wife’s birthday and she loved it!  Garlic bread is delicious. Smoked Manhattan is seductive.  Salads were perfect.  I had gnocchi for the first time and it was wonderful!  Salmon was superb.  Chocolate torte was very rich.  Service be Dani was attentive and great!   Great first visit.  We will be back!
title: Plate Restaurant - Leawood

name: Gerould Sabin
text:
We had a family gathering of seven and a baby and asked for a reservation at 5:30. It seemed odd that it took a managers approval to make the reservation, but when we arrived, they ushered us into a lovely glassed in semi-private room. This was delightful! But the service and the staff exceeded everyone’s expectations, and then the food arrived! Wow!
We recommend Plate Restaurant in Leawood and will be back regularly, not just for special events.
title: Plate Restaurant - Leawood

name: Jasmine B
text: Fresh and well seasoned! I like the aesthetic of the restaurant as well. It’s very cool and modern, also wasn’t crowded when I went on a Saturday. It is pricey, but worth trying.
title: Plate Restaurant - Leawood

name: Emily Vainer
text: Reasonably good food, not incredible, but nothing to really complain about. A bit pricey for lunch portions. Decent service, friendly staff.
title: Plate Restaurant - Leawood

name: Deidra Wright
text: I love this place, I went for my birthday dinner. Everyone was super nice and attentive. The food was absolutely delicious.
title: Plate Restaurant - Leawood

name: Hannah
text: Very beautiful atmosphere and impeccable service. We came on a busy Saturday night and were able to find seating at the bar. Delicious appetizers and cocktails
title: Plate Restaurant - Leawood

name: Jennifer Chao
text: I stayed at the hotel nearby and came in for a couple of meals because it was so good! The service was amazing and everything we had was absolutely delicious. I tried the pasta, the starters, the GARLIC BREAD!!!, even a salad and it was great. They make everything from scratch and it's incredible. I will definitely be returning.
title: Plate Restaurant - Leawood

name: Chris Bryant
text: THE BEST Italian food, along with the best service I’ve ever had. Amazing pizza, pasta, and filet. The service is second to none.
title: Plate Restaurant - Leawood

name: Christina
text: The entire staff was attentive and so friendly. I’ve never experienced such outstanding customer service. Will definitely be returning!
title: Plate Restaurant - Leawood

name: John Lair
text: Service was excellent but a lil pricey. Expected more for the price we paid.  But overall a good experience.
title: Plate Restaurant - Leawood

name: Nicci McMillian
text: Really enjoyed the food and the nice atmosphere.
title: Plate Restaurant - Leawood

name: natasha goldman
text: Awesome hospitality, food and drinks
title: Plate Restaurant - Leawood

name: Drew Le Lieu
text: One of the best overall dining experiences! Waitress Michelle was welcoming, attentive, genuine, and clearly loves creating the guest experience.  True example of luxury service. The food was absolutely delicious.  The meatballs, truffle garlic bread, house made pasta, and KC strip is some of the best in Kansas City. The lemon ice cream sandwich was simply divine! You don't have to like lemon to enjoy this refreshing dessert,  the perfect end to the savory dishes. Shout out to Pastry Master Talent Nikki! We can't wait to come back!!!
title: Plate Restaurant - Leawood
